<div class="title aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">

  <div class="h2">

    
    <div class="jumpmark" id="-1544927781" data-title="Create global impact. With us."></div>

    <div class="cmp-title">
      <h2 class="cmp-title__text">
        Create global impact. With us.
        
        
        
      </h2>
      
    </div>

  </div>
  
    


</div>
<div class="richtext aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">

  <mr-e-text class="cmp-text">
    <p>Specialists from more than 80+ fields of expertise work side-by-side at Munich Re to identify risks. Whether you specialise in mathematics, data science, computer science, IT, IoT, engineering, law or economics, <strong>we value vision, drive and diverse talents and skills</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>We are invested in our people and their growth</strong>, both in their careers and their personal lives. Our corporate culture values performance and nurtures mutual <strong>respect and trust</strong> – all of which makes <strong>sharing and expanding knowledge</strong> a great experience. And, it helps Munich Re maintain its competitive edge. &nbsp;</p>

  </mr-e-text>
  
    


</div>

</div><script>_satellite["_runScript1"](function(event, target, Promise) {
/*
 * actions is the list of flourish events that we want to catch and forward to Launch.
 * available actions are one of "mouse_enter", "mouse_leave", "click", "key_down", "play", "pause", or "change_slide"
*/
const actions = ['click', 'change_slide', 'play', 'pause']

window.addEventListener("message",(event) => {
  if (event.origin !== "https://flo.uri.sh") return;
  try {
    const data = JSON.parse(event.data)
    if (actions.includes(data.action)) {
      const flourish_event = new CustomEvent("flourish", { detail: data });
      document.dispatchEvent(flourish_event)
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error(error)
  }
})
});</script><script>_satellite["_runScript2"](function(event, target, Promise) {
const uc_link = document.querySelector('a[href="#CookieSettings"]')
uc_link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
  // preventDefault() verhindert das Standardverhalten des Browsers, den Link zu öffnen...
    e.preventDefault()
    // und hier triggern wir nun etwas anderes...
    if (UC_UI) {
        UC_UI.showSecondLayer()
    }
})
});</script>
